input:
The first line contains two integers N and M (N, M ≤ 50) that represent the dimensions of the labyrinth. The next N lines contains M characters that describe the labyrinth, the characters are of type:


	# - wall; 
	a, b, c, d - the types of keys that may exist in the labyrinth; 
	A, B, C, D - the types of doors that may exist in the labyrinth; 
	T - the initial position of Thanos; 
	p, t, m, e, r- the jewels of power, time, mind, space, and reality. 
	. - free space.
